    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic </strong>open by squashing them with the side of a knife and discard the skins</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into strips</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-and-red-pepper-linguine-with-pistachio-crumb/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> onion wedges</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>pepper strips </strong>and <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until the vegetables have softened \u2013 this is your <strong>softened veg</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-and-red-pepper-linguine-with-pistachio-crumb/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>pistachio nuts</strong> finely</p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped pistachio nuts</strong> and cook for an initial 1-2 min or until beginning to toast</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-and-red-pepper-linguine-with-pistachio-crumb/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once lightly toasted, add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> to the pan with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until the breadcrumbs are golden</p><p>Once golden, add your <strong>dried basil</strong>, stir it all together and remove from the heat \u2013 this is your <strong>pistachio crumb</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-and-red-pepper-linguine-with-pistachio-crumb/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water </strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> pasta </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>pasta</strong>, reserving a cup of the starchy pasta water</p><p>Tip: It doesn't need to be fully cooked, as it will finish cooking in the sauce later!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-and-red-pepper-linguine-with-pistachio-crumb/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>softened veg</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with your <strong>creamy single soy</strong>, <strong>balsamic sun-dried tomato paste</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and a very generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Blitz until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy tomato & red pepper sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-and-red-pepper-linguine-with-pistachio-crumb/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>drained pasta </strong>to the pot and add the <strong>creamy tomato & red pepper sauce</strong>,<strong> </strong>a good grind of <strong>pepper</strong> and a splash of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Stir it all together and cook for a final 3-4 min or until the sauce has thickened and the pasta is fully coated \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy tomato & red pepper pasta</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> salad </strong>then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-and-red-pepper-linguine-with-pistachio-crumb/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy tomato & red pepper pasta </strong>topped with the<strong> pistachio crumb</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>salad</strong>, a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
